TOKENSERVICE

The error ReferenceError: localStorage is not defined occurs because localStorage is not available in server-side rendering (SSR) environments, such as Angular Universal. When running on the server, localStorage is not defined because it is a browser-specific API.

To fix this issue, you need to ensure that localStorage is only accessed in the browser environment. Here's how you can handle this:

Solution: Check for Browser Environment
Update your TokenService to check if the code is running in the browser before accessing localStorage.

Updated TokenService
